The paper deals with the problem of estimating linear queries with local differential privacy, which involves techniques from information theory (cs.IT), data structures (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), cryptography (cs.CR), and data mining (cs.DM). The paper also cites related work from these sub-fields, further supporting their relevance.
